  "_meta": {
    "purpose": "Rough population baselines for common B2B firmographic dimensions. Used by the antagonist skill for base-rate tests. These are approximations compiled from public distributions (Census Bureau County Business Patterns for US firms, Crunchbase funding-stage distributions for venture-backed companies, BuiltWith/Datanyze tech adoption telemetry, SEC filings for public/private split). Precision is ±5 percentage points. When the antagonist needs a sharper number, it should say so rather than pretend the baseline is exact.",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "last_updated": "2026-04-23",
    "sources": [
      "US Census County Business Patterns 2023",
      "Crunchbase venture-backed company dataset 2024 snapshot",
      "BuiltWith technology distribution public aggregates",
      "SEC EDGAR public-company registrations"
    ],
    "usage_notes": [
      "These baselines represent the BROADER B2B POPULATION, not the 'plausibly targetable' B2B universe. When a user's TAM is e.g. 'venture-backed SaaS only', the antagonist should note this and adjust judgment accordingly.",
      "Baselines for US-specific dimensions (state, city) assume a US-heavy target market. For international deployments, the antagonist should flag that US-state match rates are meaningless and fall back to Test 2c.",
      "If a dimension the antagonist needs is missing, it should apply the stricter raw-threshold fallback (Test 2c in the antagonist skill) rather than invent a baseline."
    ]
  },

